name: Perancak Sunset Point
address: Unnamed Road,, Perancak, Kec. Jembrana, Kabupaten Jembrana, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: Many beautiful and colorful boats here. Normally if we come early in the morning and not during Balinese  holiday, we can find the fishermen returning and bringing many kinds of fresh seafood that we can buy.
review 2: Beautiful strip of land which divides the river on one side and the sea on the other. Photogenic boats with fishermen activities and young boys flying gigantic kites. A hidden gem for sure.
review 3: At low tide, full moon or on holidays when the fishing boats do not go out to fish, the estuary of the Perancak river is full of beautifully decorated boats. The sun sets behind the opposite side of the river. Locals and tourists go to the Perancak beach to wait for a colorful or dramatic sunset across the river. There is a restaurant where you can have dinner with fish and drinks at a reasonable price.
review 4: Beautiful sunset point, seafood bbq with sambal at a local warung, stranded boats in the river mouth. Worth a drive!
review 5:
Good place for watching sunset.
Should concern to its cleanliness.
And maybe, will look better when it has tourist attraction here.
